HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 75
By Hurt
A RESOLUTION to honor the memory of Ellie Claire Young.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly were greatly saddened to learn of
the passing of Ellie Claire Young; and
WHEREAS, a beautiful, bright light who made an impact on many people in her short
life, Ellie Claire Young was an exemplary individualâ€”smart, beautiful, witty, strong-willed,
selfless, and kind; and
WHEREAS, a special young lady who sought to help others in their time of need, Ms.
Young was taken from us at the young age of twenty-two, a victim of domestic violence; and
WHEREAS, the daughter of David and Kim Young, Ellie Claire Young was valedictorian
of her class at Halls High School and graduated with honors from the University of Tennessee
at Martin; and
WHEREAS, driven by a desire to serve her community through becoming a physician,
Ms. Young was pursuing a degree in medicine at the University of Tennessee Health Science
Center; and
WHEREAS, Ellie Claire Young was deeply devoted to her family, and she always
endeavored to remain true to family values of the highest order; and
WHEREAS, in addition to her parents, she is survived by her sister and brother-in-law,
Erin Young and Zach Harris; her grandparents, Debra Younger, Clara Young, and David "Bud"
Young, Jr.; a number of aunts and uncles, including Colt Younger, Miguel Sanchez, Donald
Young, and Kelli Young; her cousins, Callie Young, Cruz Young, and Jessica Young; and a host
of extended family members and dear friends; and
